	   <tr><td colspan=2>I know what you mean about abandoning one's bard for a while.&nbsp;&nbsp;The mid-to-late-teens were REALLY frustrating, and I went and worked on my warrior for a while.  All I can say is hang in there....  When we (my Pally partner and I) hit 18 we went to Lake of Ill Omen.  Through careful grouping and doing a little duoing along the shoreline we've just Dinged 25.<br><br>When you hit 20 groups start really loving you because you get Chant of Clarity (same effect as the Clarity spell).  Twist it with Anthem and Hymn when in groups who can mezz, then just sit back and rake in the XP.  You keep everyone's health up (taking the burden off of Clerics except for major damage), give your fighters a great strength buff, and Clarity keeps your casters' mana from draining so fast.  Keep your drums handy in case you need to run (always know where your escape path is!), but in a good group you'll take minimal damage.<br><br>Yup, I'd say that 20 is when being a Bard becomes less frustrating.  I can't WAIT until my late-20's songs!<br><br>A suggestion for folks going to far-off lands to level:  research and buy your next 5 or 10 songs and stick 'em in the bank.  There's no Bard Guild on Kunark (just an outpost selling +50 songs).  It's much handier to run to the nearest bank for your next song than across the world.<br><br>Calthine<br>Bard of the 25th song<br>Vazelle<br>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://calthine.tripod.com target=_new>Calthine Faeriesong</a><br>52 Minstrel of <a href=HTTP://www.tortureguild.org target=_new>Torture</a><br>Vazelle</td></tr>
