	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Feb 7th 2:06 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The beauty of Everquest is the versatility of the game.&nbsp;&nbsp;To answer your question... there is no answer.  Try new things, experiment with new weapons, and most of all have a great time doing it.<br><br>Now, since I know for a fact that wasn't what you wanted to hear, here's the real answer:  Many people wield piercing weapons either because of class limitations or because of the low delay.  1hs is one of the more versatile weapon classes in terms of weapons available, and the fact that (as a bard) you will get dual wield at level 17, it seems like 1hs would be a decent bet.  2hs-ers can do some serious damage but are usually handicapped by a very long delay.  Typically you will see characters with a much higher str stat wielding the 2hs.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
