	   <tr><td colspan=2>My bard just recently picked up baking.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is a great skill, especially if you can forage.  Supplies are inexpensive (although I did learn pottery to make my baking dishes).  The bonus:  baked food all weighs 0.1, almost everything you can forage or loot that isn't edible (lion and other types of meat) and be turned into multple meals at little expense, and many baked items give you stat increases.  The party is always impressed when you pass out +3 STR mammoth steaks....<br><br>Calthine, Bard of the 22nd Song<br>Vazelle <br>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://calthine.tripod.com target=_new>Calthine Faeriesong</a><br>52 Minstrel of <a href=HTTP://www.tortureguild.org target=_new>Torture</a><br>Vazelle</td></tr>
