	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jan 25th 4:34 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.71]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At L11 near Queynos the best choice is probably hunting gnolls in Blackburrow. Gnolls come in anything from L5 to L15. Beware of the ever present trains, though.<br>Alternatively you can go to Everfrost and get a mammoth calf group.<br><br>As Brusco's goes, i personally never used it much. It is nice for pulling around your level, but if you have a decent weapon you will gain more by twisting Jonathan's, Chant of Battle and Hymn of Restoration.<br>In a group, replace Jonathans's with Anthem.<br><br>Nothe that a lot of people swear on twisting Brusco's in, its a matter of personal preference. Also the weapon you use makes a huge difference in usefulness. I twinked my bard with a crystal spider fang at like 14 and the damage output from this makes Brusco's pretty insignificant.<br><br>One other application is kiting a mob with Brusco's, which is difficult to master, and usually not very effective. However, if you see you are just barely on the loosing side in a fight, kick in selos, run away a bit, use brusco's, twist with hymn and selo's, always keeping out of the MOBs range. Usually you can change the odds far enough to win the fight.<br>&nbsp;<br>Nindor<br>L65 Dwarven Cleric on Zebuxoruk<br>Stone</td></tr>
