	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102027780765647><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102027780765647>RE: Equipment Help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102027780765647#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=113466><span id=Sage>rutkoskyd</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>62 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 1st 2:30 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.36]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I sorta feel like I'm saying the same thing in most of my posts about bards, but here goes...&nbsp;&nbsp;Bards are the epitome of versatility.  You can deal out damage, heal, be a manabattery, pull, and run crowd control.  The equipment you choose should mirror the role that you find yourself in the majority of the time.  But don't make yourself one-sided--you never know when you may be called upon to fill one of the many roles you're able to perform.  With that being said, a good rule of thumb is to know that you are a singer that can fight, not a fighter that can sing.  Keep your AC and your resistances high.  Cha is also important, but don't sacrifice your str, AC, or resists just so you can top the 200 mark.  This is an option, of course, but when you become higher level and you see the pretty boy bards who just sit back and play manasong, never once equipping their weapons, you'll understand.<br><br>I'd hit the earrrings first.  Go for a couple cougar claw earrings if you can, orc fangs as a replacement.  Leave your face slot alone--you'll be getting your Mask of Deception soon enough, which packs a wicked 4 AC and 13 Cha.  Chest slot's good for now, but I'd go for a skull-shaped barbute on your head.  When you hit your lower-mid 20s head over to Frontier Mountains and camp the giants.  They'll occasionally drop a Straw Spun Belt which is 10 AC.  I have noticed that your cha seems a bit low, so you may look at getting an Electrum Star Ruby ring.  They're 5 Dex 7 Cha, but a bit spendy.  I know you're on a budget.  Your gear upgrade should be done gradually starting with AC upgrades first.  Hope this helps a bit.  <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
