	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have to disagree with a portion of this post.&nbsp;&nbsp;While I am not arguing BardofDreams opinion of the best race (although I disagree), I do have to argue this comment:<br><br>&quot;a vash shir is also a good race for a bard the only problem is its hard to vlvl there but if you can lvl to 20 with a vash shir bard they rule but to lvl 20 it takes 80 hours&quot;<br><br>I have under 14 hours played with my Vah Shir Bard and I am at level 8.  Multiply it out at that rate (31 hours), and even with a progressive slow-down, one should be able to hit 20 within about 40 hours.<br><br>With the ability to solo blues and whites consistently, and even take yellows occasionally, I don't really see the exp slowing down much up to 20...  Especially considering all of the new songs gained while working up to that point.<br><br>Really though, it all depends on what and how you fight.  Those things will have a far greater impact on leveling speed than any race choice could.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
